<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="236" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="29.[178,1085,380,430]" pageId="29" pageNumber="236">Etymology: The specific epithet (Latin, adjective: yellow) alludes to the uniformly yellowish coloration.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="236" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="29.[178,1085,445,555]" pageId="29" pageNumber="236">
Description: Body length 
<quantity box="[541,663,445,467]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.2" metricValueMax="3.8" metricValueMin="2.6" pageId="29" pageNumber="236" unit="mm" value="3.2" valueMax="3.8" valueMin="2.6">2.6-3.8 mm</quantity>
; length of forebody 
<quantity box="[875,996,445,467]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.45" metricValueMax="1.6" metricValueMin="1.3" pageId="29" pageNumber="236" unit="mm" value="1.45" valueMax="1.6" valueMin="1.3">1.3-1.6 mm</quantity>
. Coloration: body dark-yellowish, with the abdominal segment VI sometimes weakly infuscate in the middle; legs pale-yellowish; antennae reddish to reddish-brown, with the basal antennomeres often paler reddish and antennomere XI dark-yellowish.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[178,1085,570,768]" pageId="29" pageNumber="236">
Head (
<figureCitation box="[251,331,570,592]" captionStart="Figs 96-105" captionStartId="28.[178,218,1502,1524]" captionTargetBox="[178,1074,212,1485]" captionTargetId="figure-1@28.[178,1082,212,1493]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="Figs 96-105: Nepalota crocea nov.sp.: (96) forebody; (97) antenna; (98) male tergite VIII; (99) male sternite VIII; (100-101) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (102) paramere; (103) female tergite VIII; (104) female sternite VIII; (105) spermatheca. Scale bars: 96: 0.5 mm; 97-99, 103-104: 0.2 mm; 100-102, 105: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5414208" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5414208/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="236">Fig. 96</figureCitation>
) transverse; dorsal surface with nearly obsolete microreticulation and glossy; punctation sparse and extremely fine. Eyes large, much longer than postocular region in dorsal view. Antenna (
<figureCitation box="[518,594,629,651]" captionStart="Figs 96-105" captionStartId="28.[178,218,1502,1524]" captionTargetBox="[178,1074,212,1485]" captionTargetId="figure-1@28.[178,1082,212,1493]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="Figs 96-105: Nepalota crocea nov.sp.: (96) forebody; (97) antenna; (98) male tergite VIII; (99) male sternite VIII; (100-101) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (102) paramere; (103) female tergite VIII; (104) female sternite VIII; (105) spermatheca. Scale bars: 96: 0.5 mm; 97-99, 103-104: 0.2 mm; 100-102, 105: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5414208" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5414208/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="236">Fig. 97</figureCitation>
) approximately 0.9-1.0 mm long; antennomere IV weakly oblong or approximately as long as broad; antennomeres V-X of gradually increasing width and increasingly transverse; preapical antennomeres distinctly transverse, nearly 1.5 times as broad as long; antennomere XI apically acute, slightly shorter than the combined length of VIII-X.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[178,1085,783,864]" pageId="29" pageNumber="236">
Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[294,371,783,805]" captionStart="Figs 96-105" captionStartId="28.[178,218,1502,1524]" captionTargetBox="[178,1074,212,1485]" captionTargetId="figure-1@28.[178,1082,212,1493]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="Figs 96-105: Nepalota crocea nov.sp.: (96) forebody; (97) antenna; (98) male tergite VIII; (99) male sternite VIII; (100-101) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (102) paramere; (103) female tergite VIII; (104) female sternite VIII; (105) spermatheca. Scale bars: 96: 0.5 mm; 97-99, 103-104: 0.2 mm; 100-102, 105: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5414208" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5414208/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="236">Fig. 96</figureCitation>
) large and strongly transverse, 1.30-1.35 times as broad as long and 1.4-1.5 times as broad as head, without sexual dimorphism; disc with nearly obsolete microreticulation, glossy, and with extremely fine punctation.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[178,1085,879,930]" pageId="29" pageNumber="236">
Elytra (
<figureCitation box="[258,336,879,901]" captionStart="Figs 96-105" captionStartId="28.[178,218,1502,1524]" captionTargetBox="[178,1074,212,1485]" captionTargetId="figure-1@28.[178,1082,212,1493]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="Figs 96-105: Nepalota crocea nov.sp.: (96) forebody; (97) antenna; (98) male tergite VIII; (99) male sternite VIII; (100-101) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (102) paramere; (103) female tergite VIII; (104) female sternite VIII; (105) spermatheca. Scale bars: 96: 0.5 mm; 97-99, 103-104: 0.2 mm; 100-102, 105: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5414208" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5414208/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="236">Fig. 96</figureCitation>
) approximately as long as pronotum; punctation dense and fine; interstices with shallow microreticulation. Hind wings fully developed.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[178,1085,946,997]" pageId="29" pageNumber="236">Abdomen with very shallow transverse microsculpture; punctation very sparse and fine; tergites III and VII without sexual dimorphism.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[178,1086,1012,1152]" pageId="29" pageNumber="236">
♂: tergite VIII (
<figureCitation box="[356,435,1012,1034]" captionStart="Figs 96-105" captionStartId="28.[178,218,1502,1524]" captionTargetBox="[178,1074,212,1485]" captionTargetId="figure-1@28.[178,1082,212,1493]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="Figs 96-105: Nepalota crocea nov.sp.: (96) forebody; (97) antenna; (98) male tergite VIII; (99) male sternite VIII; (100-101) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (102) paramere; (103) female tergite VIII; (104) female sternite VIII; (105) spermatheca. Scale bars: 96: 0.5 mm; 97-99, 103-104: 0.2 mm; 100-102, 105: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5414208" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5414208/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="236">Fig. 98</figureCitation>
) approximately as long as broad and with distinctly convex posterior margin; sternite VIII (
<figureCitation box="[506,582,1042,1064]" captionStart="Figs 96-105" captionStartId="28.[178,218,1502,1524]" captionTargetBox="[178,1074,212,1485]" captionTargetId="figure-1@28.[178,1082,212,1493]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="Figs 96-105: Nepalota crocea nov.sp.: (96) forebody; (97) antenna; (98) male tergite VIII; (99) male sternite VIII; (100-101) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (102) paramere; (103) female tergite VIII; (104) female sternite VIII; (105) spermatheca. Scale bars: 96: 0.5 mm; 97-99, 103-104: 0.2 mm; 100-102, 105: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5414208" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5414208/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="236">Fig. 99</figureCitation>
) approximately as long as broad, slightly longer than tergite VIII, and strongly convex posteriorly; median lobe of aedeagus (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figs 96-105" captionStartId="28.[178,218,1502,1524]" captionTargetBox="[178,1074,212,1485]" captionTargetId="figure-1@28.[178,1082,212,1493]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="Figs 96-105: Nepalota crocea nov.sp.: (96) forebody; (97) antenna; (98) male tergite VIII; (99) male sternite VIII; (100-101) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (102) paramere; (103) female tergite VIII; (104) female sternite VIII; (105) spermatheca. Scale bars: 96: 0.5 mm; 97-99, 103-104: 0.2 mm; 100-102, 105: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5414208" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5414208/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="236">Figs 100- 101</figureCitation>
) relatively small, approximately 
<quantity box="[572,666,1100,1122]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.8" pageId="29" pageNumber="236" unit="mm" value="0.38">0.38 mm</quantity>
long, of slender shape; paramere (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figs 96-105" captionStartId="28.[178,218,1502,1524]" captionTargetBox="[178,1074,212,1485]" captionTargetId="figure-1@28.[178,1082,212,1493]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="Figs 96-105: Nepalota crocea nov.sp.: (96) forebody; (97) antenna; (98) male tergite VIII; (99) male sternite VIII; (100-101) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (102) paramere; (103) female tergite VIII; (104) female sternite VIII; (105) spermatheca. Scale bars: 96: 0.5 mm; 97-99, 103-104: 0.2 mm; 100-102, 105: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5414208" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5414208/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="236">Fig. 102</figureCitation>
) approximately as long as median lobe and with slender apical lobe.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[178,1085,1167,1247]" pageId="29" pageNumber="236">
<specimenCount box="[178,199,1172,1193]" pageId="29" pageNumber="236" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
: tergite VIII (
<figureCitation box="[354,444,1167,1189]" captionStart="Figs 96-105" captionStartId="28.[178,218,1502,1524]" captionTargetBox="[178,1074,212,1485]" captionTargetId="figure-1@28.[178,1082,212,1493]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="Figs 96-105: Nepalota crocea nov.sp.: (96) forebody; (97) antenna; (98) male tergite VIII; (99) male sternite VIII; (100-101) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (102) paramere; (103) female tergite VIII; (104) female sternite VIII; (105) spermatheca. Scale bars: 96: 0.5 mm; 97-99, 103-104: 0.2 mm; 100-102, 105: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5414208" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5414208/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="236">Fig. 103</figureCitation>
) of similar shape as in male; sternite VIII (
<figureCitation box="[916,994,1167,1189]" captionStart="Figs 65-74" captionStartId="21.[178,218,1510,1532]" captionTargetBox="[182,1068,212,1485]" captionTargetId="figure-1@21.[178,1082,212,1493]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Figs 65-74: Nepalota fellowesi PACE: (65) forebody; (66) antenna; (67) male tergite VIII; (68) male sternite VIII; (69) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view; (70) apical portion of median lobe of aedeagus in ventral view; (71) paramere; (72) female tergite VIII; (73) female sternite VIII; (74) spermatheca. Scale bars: 65-66: 0.5 mm; 67-74: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5414200" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5414200/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="236">Fig. 73</figureCitation>
) weakly transverse and with broadly convex posterior margin, middle of posterior margin not concave; spermatheca (
